==Abstract==

This IIP defines a format for exporting and importing wallet labels. It implements BIP 329 for INTcoin.

==Motivation==

Users label addresses and transactions for record-keeping. A standard export format enables:
* Wallet migration
* Backup of organizational data
* Sharing labels between devices

==Specification==

===Format===

JSON Lines (JSONL) format, one object per line:

<pre>
{"type": "tx", "ref": "<txid>", "label": "<label>"}
{"type": "addr", "ref": "<address>", "label": "<label>"}
{"type": "pubkey", "ref": "<pubkey_hex>", "label": "<label>"}
{"type": "input", "ref": "<txid>:<vout>", "label": "<label>"}
{"type": "output", "ref": "<txid>:<vout>", "label": "<label>"}
{"type": "xpub", "ref": "<extended_pubkey>", "label": "<label>"}
</pre>

===Types===

{| class="wikitable"
|-
! Type !! Reference Format !! Description
|-
| tx || txid (64 hex chars) || Transaction label
|-
| addr || Bech32m address || Address label
|-
| pubkey || hex-encoded pubkey || Public key label
|-
| input || txid:vout || Input label
|-
| output || txid:vout || Output label
|-
| xpub || ixpub... || Extended public key label
|}

===Optional Fields===

<pre>
{
  "type": "addr",
  "ref": "int1q...",
  "label": "Cold storage",
  "spendable": true,
  "origin": "m/44'/2210'/0'/0/0"
}
</pre>

===File Extension===

Recommended: .labels.jsonl

===Example===

<pre>
{"type":"addr","ref":"int1qr7vy6sqrl8y22zl6rzw59v07e6r3k9unuwe3r9v2snz30swzaqw7wwd24y","label":"Donation address"}
{"type":"tx","ref":"abc123...","label":"Payment to vendor"}
{"type":"addr","ref":"int1q...","label":"Exchange deposit","origin":"m/44'/2210'/0'/0/5"}
</pre>

